# Trivy ignore list for the worker image.
#
# Every entry must include a justification and an expiry. Review on every
# worker-image bump; delete entries whose underlying fix has landed.

# --- gopls pulls github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk v0.8.0 as a
# transitive dep; v1.3.1/1.4.0/1.4.1 fix the CVEs below. gopls v0.21.1 is
# the latest release and has not yet bumped the dep. We ship gopls only so
# Claude Code can drive LSP operations inside the container workspace --
# it never terminates network connections itself, so the DNS-rebinding /
# case-sensitivity / null-byte parsing issues are not reachable from the
# sandbox. Accepted until gopls upstream bumps.
CVE-2026-27896
CVE-2026-33252
CVE-2026-34742
GHSA-q382-vc8q-7jhj

# --- @anthropic-ai/claude-code@2.1.116 pulls picomatch 4.0.3 as an npm
# transitive; 4.0.4 fixes the ReDoS. Upstream claude-code has not yet
# published a version that picks up the newer picomatch. Worker
# container is single-tenant and the allowlist restricts which globs
# are ever parsed, so the ReDoS is not reachable from a prompt
# attacker.
CVE-2026-33671
